Author Biographies
Dennis Coates is a Professor of Economics, University of Maryland, Baltimore County. He loves sports but hates public policy based on self-serving economic impact reports.
Bernd Frick is a Professor of organizational, media, and sports economics and a Vice President at the University of Paderborn. Moreover, he is director of the Institute of Labor and Personnel Management at Mobile Life Campus of Volkswagen AG in Wolfsburg. When younger, he was a mediocre football player and a competitive marathon runner. Although somewhat slower today, he continues to be a dedicated runner.
Todd Jewell is a professor of finance and economics at Texas State University - San Marcos. He currently serves as department chair. His research has covered US collegiate and professional sports in the US and the UK.

